Canada (BC): Norovirus Infection of Oysters Suspected Cause of Gastroenteritis
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The British Columbia Centre for Disease Control (BCCD) has confirmed that
oysters are behind a rash of illnesses reported over the past couple of
months. The BCCDC issued an advisory last month warning people to cook all
oysters before eating them. But until now, tests had not conclusively
linked the illnesses to oysters.
BCCDC epidemiologist Laura McDougall says the problem is the common
norovirus that is passed among humans. But McDougall says it's not possible
to confirm the presence of the virus in the oysters themselves. "We do have
test limitations on being able to do that," she says. "We have been able to
detect the virus in clinical samples - samples from human that became ill."
McDougall says the number of cases of norovirus illness being reported has
dropped off dramatically in the last few weeks.
--
