Russia (Sverdlovsk Region: Outbreak of Rotavirus Enteritis Infection in Irbit
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
In the city of Irbit (Sverdlovsk region) 154 people were hospitalized as a
result of an outbreak of intestinal infection, according to a statement by
Sanitary epidemiological center physician Alexandr Rostyuk. "At the present
time, 154 people are hospitalized, of them 113 are children under 2 years
old. Most of the victims are suffering with rotavirus enteritis".
According to his statement, the rise in intestinal infections has occurred
since 9 Feb 2004. Condition of those hospitalized is characterized as
moderate, said the chief physician of the hospital.
Drinking water cleaning and chlorination measures were launched in the
city, physicians are recommending not to use raw drinking water, but to use
boiled water only and obey basic sanitary hygiene rules. At the present
time. Twelve kindergarten in the city are under quarantine, added Rostyuk.
He indicated that the outbreak of intestinal infection was due to
contamination of the public drinking water supply by contamination of the
system by spring flood water.
